  "prompt": "Can I use a same mobile number for two accounts in sbi for internet banking?",
  "response": "No, you **cannot use the same mobile number for two different accounts in SBI for Internet Banking**. State Bank of India (SBI) requires a unique mobile number to be linked to each account for security and authentication purposes. This is because the mobile number is used for One-Time Passwords (OTP) and other account-related notifications.\n\nIf you try to register the same mobile number for a second account, the system will likely reject the request or deactivate the previous registration.\n\n### What Can You Do?\n1. **Use Different Mobile Numbers**: If you have two accounts, you must link them to separate mobile numbers.\n2. **Update Mobile Number**: If you want to change the mobile number linked to one of your accounts, you can do so by visiting an SBI branch or using the YONO app (if eligible).\n\nFor further assistance, you can contact SBI customer care or visit your nearest branch.",
